Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of multiple-antenna transmitter cooperation in wireless networks to avoid interference, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses the practicality and scalability of transmitter cooperation approaches, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the allocation of feedback to transmitters, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG) depending on the specific techniques used.
